vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}

title: "Static vs Dynamic Tree Decision" {
  near: top-center
  shape: text
  style: {
    font-size: 32
    bold: true
    underline: true
  }
}

# Decision states
decision: "Workload Analysis" {
  shape: diamond
  style: {
    fill: "#E8F4FD"
    stroke: "#0EA5E9"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

# Question branches
decision -> static_check: "Data changes\nafter build?" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#0EA5E9"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

static_check: "No / Rarely" {
  shape: diamond
  style: {
    fill: "#FEF3C7"
    stroke: "#F59E0B"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

decision -> updates_check: "Yes / Frequently" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#0EA5E9"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

updates_check: "Update\nFrequency?" {
  shape: diamond
  style: {
    fill: "#FEF3C7"
    stroke: "#F59E0B"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

# vEB path (static data)
static_check -> veb_optimal: "vEB Layout\nOPTIMAL" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#10B981"
    stroke-width: 3
    bold: true
  }
}

veb_optimal: ||md
**van Emde Boas Layout**
✓ O(log_B N) cache misses
✓ Parameter-free optimality
✓ Single allocation
✓ Best for read-heavy workloads

**Use when:**
- Dictionaries, static indices
- Symbol tables
- Read-only databases
|| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#D1FAE5"
    stroke: "#10B981"
    stroke-width: 3
  }
}

# Update frequency split
updates_check -> moderate_check: "Moderate\n(< 10%)" {
  style.stroke: "#F59E0B"
}
updates_check -> high_check: "High\n(> 10%)" {
  style.stroke: "#F59E0B"
}

moderate_check: "Size of\ndata?" {
  shape: diamond
  style: {
    fill: "#FEF3C7"
    stroke: "#F59E0B"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

high_check: "Latency\nRequirement?" {
  shape: diamond
  style: {
    fill: "#FEF3C7"
    stroke: "#F59E0B"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

# Hybrid path (moderate updates, large data)
moderate_check -> hybrid_approach: "Large\n(> 1M)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#8B5CF6"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

hybrid_approach: ||md
**Hybrid Approach**
vEB + Overflow Buffer

1. Build vEB from sorted data
2. Buffer new inserts separately
3. Periodic rebuild when buffer > threshold

**Trade-off:** Amortized O(log_B N) lookups 
with batch rebuild cost
|| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#EDE9FE"
    stroke: "#8B5CF6"
    stroke-width: 3
  }
}

# B-tree path (moderate updates, small data)
moderate_check -> btree_approach: "Small\n(< 1M)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#F59E0B"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

btree_approach: ||md
**B-Tree (Tuned)**
✓ O(log_B N) cache misses
✓ Efficient inserts/deletes
✗ Requires cache-line tuning

Node size = cache line size
Branching factor = 16 (typical)
|| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#FEF3C7"
    stroke: "#F59E0B"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

# Latency-based decision for high updates
high_check -> pointer_bst: "Simple\n(Fast dev)" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#EF4444"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

high_check -> btree_dynamic: "Performance\ncritical" {
  style: {
    stroke: "#3B82F6"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

pointer_bst: ||md
**Pointer BST**
✗ O(log N) cache misses (worst)
✓ Simple insert/delete
✓ Self-balancing variants
✓ Low implementation cost

**Acceptable when:**
- Cache misses tolerable
- Development speed priority
- Data fits in cache
|| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#FEE2E2"
    stroke: "#EF4444"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}

btree_dynamic: ||md
**B-Tree / B+Tree**
✓ O(log_B N) cache misses
✓ Efficient bulk operations
✓ Range queries (B+Tree)

**Best for:**
- Databases, filesystems
- Write-heavy workloads
- Ordered traversals
|| {
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#DBEAFE"
    stroke: "#3B82F6"
    stroke-width: 3
  }
}

# Summary box
summary: ||md
**Cache Complexity Summary**

| Structure | Cache Misses | Insert | Delete |
|-----------|--------------|--------|--------|
| vEB | O(log_B N) | O(N) | O(N) |
| B-Tree | O(log_B N) | O(log_B N) | O(log_B N) |
| Pointer BST | O(log N) | O(log N) | O(log N) |
| Hybrid | O(log_B N)* | O(1)* | O(N)* |

*\*Amortized with periodic rebuild*
|| {
  near: bottom-center
  shape: rectangle
  style: {
    fill: "#F3F4F6"
    stroke: "#6B7280"
    stroke-width: 2
  }
}